<s> Finally, plaintiff's claim that defendants exceeded the scope of its license ?[**19]? agreements states a claim for copyright infringement rather than breach of contract.  </s>
<s> Not being parties to any license agreement with Microsoft, defendants are "complete strangers" to Microsoft, and their violations of the licensing restrictions must of necessity be seen as claims arising under the copyright laws rather than the law of contracts.  </s>
